This directory contains the python scripts in the PmagPy software distribution
by "Lisa Tauxe" <ltauxe@ucsd.edu>.

Complete documentation is available at: http://magician.ucsd.edu/Software/PmagPy

To install, first grab the latest pip for your platform (http://www.pip-installer.org/).
E.g.: once you have Python installed Windows or Mac, run `easy_install pip`.
On debian-based Linux distributions; run: `sudo apt-get install python-pip`.

Next, run `pip install -r requirements.txt`. You may find it easier/quicker to get pre-built binaries for your distro.

Finally, run: `pip install git+https://github.com/ltauxe/PmagPy#egg=pmagpy`.

